text: Nuestra Señora de La Paz (; ; )Yaticha Kamani / Ministerio de Educación, Aymara aru thakhinchawi, Chuqi Yapu 2011 is the capital of Bolivia, and La Paz Department. It is the second largest city (in people) only after Santa Cruz de la Sierra. It is in the western part of the country in the department of the same name. It is at an elevation of above sea level, making it the world's highest de facto capital city. == References == Category:Cities in Bolivia Category:National capitals in South America Category:1540s establishments in South America Category:La Paz Department (Bolivia)
